#. type: YAML Front Matter: title
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Load Shedding reference guide"
msgstr "限电参考指南"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "<a class=\"status-label status-experimental\" title=\"This extension requests early feedback to mature the idea\" href=\"#extension-status-note\">experimental</a>"
msgstr "<a class=\"status-label status-experimental\" title=\"此扩展程序希望征集早期反馈以完善该构想\" href=\"#extension-status-note\">实验性</a>"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Load shedding is the practice of detecting service overload and rejecting requests.\n"
"By rejecting requests when overloaded, load shedding keeps the application alive.\n"
"With priority load shedding, the application even keeps working, albeit in a degraded state: only a fraction of requests is handled, others are rejected early.\n"
"You should consider using it if your application runs in a dynamic environment with a real risk of getting overloaded and is not fronted by another service that sheds load already."
msgstr "负载分流是指检测服务过载并拒绝请求的做法。通过在过载时拒绝请求，负载分流能确保应用程序保持运行。采用优先级负载分流时，应用程序甚至能在性能降级状态下继续运行：仅处理其中一部分请求，其余请求则会被提前拒绝。 如果您的应用程序运行在动态环境中，且确实存在过载的风险，同时前面没有其他服务负责进行负载分流，那么您应该考虑使用该机制。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "In Quarkus, the `quarkus-load-shedding` extension provides a load shedding mechanism."
msgstr "在 Quarkus 中 `，quarkus-load-shedding` 扩展提供了一种负载分流机制。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Use the Load Shedding extension"
msgstr "使用“Load Shedding”扩展"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "To use the load shedding extension, you need to add the `io.quarkus:quarkus-load-shedding` extension to your project:"
msgstr "要使用负载分流扩展，您需要将 `io.quarkus:quarkus-load-shedding` 扩展添加到您的项目中："

#. type: Block title
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "pom.xml"
msgstr "pom.xml"

#. type: Block title
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "build.gradle"
msgstr "build.gradle"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When added, load shedding is enabled.\n"
"It can be disabled by setting `quarkus.load-shedding.enabled` to `false`."
msgstr "添加后，将启用负载分流功能。可通过将 `quarkus.load-shedding.enabled` 设置为 `false` 来禁用该功能。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There are 2 variants of load shedding: pure and priority-based.\n"
"Pure load shedding rejects all requests when overload is detected.\n"
"Priority load shedding only rejects a fraction of requests even if overload is detected, based on application-defined criteria.\n"
"By default, priority load shedding is enabled.\n"
"It can be disabled by setting `quarkus.load-shedding.priority.enabled` to `false.`"
msgstr "负载卸载有两种变体：纯卸载和基于优先级的卸载。 纯负载分流在检测到过载时会拒绝所有请求。优先级负载分流即使检测到过载，也会根据应用程序定义的标准仅拒绝部分请求。默认情况下，优先级负载分流处于启用状态。可通过将 `quarkus.load-shedding.priority.enabled` 设置为 `false` 来禁用该功能 `。`"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "There are 2 ways of customizing priority load shedding:"
msgstr "自定义优先级限电有以下两种方法："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "By implementing `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestPrioritizer`, the application can decide which requests can be rejected early on and which requests can only be rejected when there's no other choice."
msgstr "通过实现 `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestPrioritizer，` 应用程序可以决定哪些请求可以在早期被拒绝，哪些请求只能在别无选择时才被拒绝。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "By implementing `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestClassifier`, the application can classify requests into cohorts which are rejected independently."
msgstr "通过实现 `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestClassifier` ，应用程序可以将请求分类到不同的组中，这些组将分别被拒绝。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Other configuration options are described below, although they should typically be left untouched."
msgstr "下面将介绍其他配置选项，不过通常情况下应保持这些选项的默认设置不变。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The load shedding algorithm"
msgstr "限电算法"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "The load shedding algorithm has 2 parts:"
msgstr "限电算法包括两个部分："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "overload detection"
msgstr "过载检测"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "priority load shedding (optional)"
msgstr "优先限电（可选）"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Overload detection"
msgstr "过载检测"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "To detect whether the current service is overloaded, an adaptation of TCP Vegas is used."
msgstr "为了检测当前服务是否过载，采用了TCP Vegas算法的变体。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This algorithm starts with a configurable limit of in-flight requests, by default 100.\n"
"If the current number of concurrent in-flight requests reaches the limit, overload situation is signalled."
msgstr "该算法首先设定一个可配置的“处理中请求”上限，默认值为100。如果当前并发处理中请求的数量达到该上限，则会触发过载警报。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That is not very interesting, but the algorithm dynamically adjusts the limit based on the size of the request queue.\n"
"If the queue is short, more requests can be handled and the limit increases; if the queue is long, fewer requests can be handled and the limit decreases.\n"
"The limit cannot be increased indefinitely; there's a configurable maximum, by default 1000."
msgstr "这虽然没什么特别有趣的，但该算法会根据请求队列的长度动态调整限制值。如果队列较短，则可处理的请求更多，限制值随之增加；如果队列较长，则可处理的请求较少，限制值随之减少。 该限制不能无限提高；有一个可配置的最大值，默认值为1000。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There's no actual queue of requests that we could monitor, though, so the algorithm estimates the current length of a request queue based on previously seen response times.\n"
"The longer recent requests take, compared to the recent lowest response time, the longer the queue is supposed to be."
msgstr "不过，实际上并没有我们可以监控的请求队列，因此该算法会根据之前观察到的响应时间来估算当前请求队列的长度。与最近的最低响应时间相比，如果近期请求的耗时越长，则推测队列就越长。"

#. type: Title ==
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Priority load shedding"
msgstr "优先限电"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "If an overload situation is signalled, priority load shedding is invoked."
msgstr "如果检测到过载情况，将启动优先限电措施。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If priority load shedding is disabled, there's nothing to do and all requests are rejected immediately.\n"
"However, by default, priority load shedding is enabled, which means a request is only rejected if the current CPU load is high enough."
msgstr "如果禁用了优先级负载分流，则无需采取任何措施，所有请求都会被立即拒绝。不过，默认情况下，优先级负载分流是启用的，这意味着只有当当前 CPU 负载足够高时，请求才会被拒绝。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Priority load shedding is currently always based on CPU load.\n"
"Other mechanisms are possible (such as network utilization), but currently not implemented."
msgstr "目前，优先级负载削减始终基于 CPU 负载。虽然也可以采用其他机制（例如网络利用率），但目前尚未实现。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "To determine whether a request should be rejected, 2 attributes are considered:"
msgstr "在确定是否应拒绝某项请求时，会考虑以下两个属性："

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "request priority"
msgstr "请求优先级"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "request cohort"
msgstr "请求队列"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "There are 5 statically defined priorities and 128 cohorts, which amounts to 640 request groups in total."
msgstr "共有 5 个静态定义的优先级和 128 个分组，共计 640 个请求组。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"After both priority and cohort are assigned to a request, a request group number is computed.\n"
"The group number is smaller for higher priority requests and higher for lower priority requests.\n"
"If the group number is higher that the current CPU load, the request is rejected, otherwise it is allowed even in an overload situation."
msgstr "在为请求分配优先级和组别后，系统会计算出一个请求组号。优先级越高的请求，其组号越小；优先级越低的请求，其组号越大。如果组号大于当前的CPU负载，则拒绝该请求；否则，即使在过载情况下，该请求也会被允许。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The group number is actually not compared to the CPU load directly; instead, it is compared to a function of CPU load.\n"
"The function is `(1 - load^3) * 640`, where `load` is the CPU load as a number between 0.0 and 1.0, and 640 is a number of requests group as mentioned above."
msgstr "该组号实际上并非直接与 CPU 负载进行比较，而是与 CPU 负载的一个函数进行比较。 该函数为 `(1 - load^3) * 640，` 其中 `load` 是 CPU 负载值（范围在 0.0 到 1.0 之间），640 则是上文提到的请求分组数量。"

#. type: Title ===
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Customizing request priority"
msgstr "自定义请求优先级"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Priority is assigned by a `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestPrioritizer`.\n"
"There is 5 statically defined priorities in the `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestPriority` enum: `CRITICAL`, `IMPORTANT`, `NORMAL`, `BACKGROUND` and `DEGRADED`.\n"
"By default, if no request prioritizer applies, the priority is assumed to be `NORMAL`."
msgstr "优先级由 `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestPrioritizer` 进行分配。 在 ` `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestPriority` ` 枚举中，有 5 个静态定义的优先级： `CRITICAL` 、 `IMPORTANT` 、 `NORMAL` 、 `BACKGROUND` 和 `DEGRADED` 。默认情况下，如果没有应用任何请求优先级分配器，则优先级默认为 `NORMAL` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There is one default prioritizer which assigns the priority of `CRITICAL` to requests to the non-application endpoints.\n"
"It declares no `@Priority`."
msgstr "有一个默认优先级分配器，它会将 `“CRITICAL”` 优先级分配给发往非应用程序端点的请求。该分配器未声明任何 `@Priority` 注解。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It is possible to define custom implementations of the `RequestPrioritizer` interface.\n"
"The implementations must be CDI beans, otherwise they are ignored.\n"
"The CDI rules of typesafe resolution must be followed.\n"
"That is, if multiple implementations exist with a different `@Priority` value and some of them are ``@Alternative``s, only the alternatives with the highest priority value are retained.\n"
"If no implementation is an alternative, all implementations are retained and are sorted in descending `@Priority` order (highest priority value comes first)."
msgstr "可以定义 `RequestPrioritizer` 接口的自定义实现。这些实现必须是 CDI Bean，否则将被忽略。必须遵循 CDI 的类型安全解析规则。也就是说，如果存在多个具有不同 `@Priority` 值的实现，且其中部分是 `@Alternatives` ，则仅保留优先级最高的替代方案。 如果没有实现是替代项，则保留所有实现，并按 `@Priority` 值从高到低排序（优先级最高的值排在最前面）。"

#. type: Title ===
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Customizing request cohort"
msgstr "自定义请求群体"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Cohort is assigned by a `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestClassifier`.\n"
"There is 128 statically defined cohorts, with the lowest number being 1 and highest number being 128.\n"
"The classifier should return a number in this interval; if it does not, the number is adjusted automatically."
msgstr "分组由 `io.quarkus.load.shedding.RequestClassifier` 进行分配。共有 128 个静态定义的分组，编号范围从 1 到 128。分类器应返回该区间内的一个数字；若未返回，系统将自动调整该数字。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There is one default classifier which assigns a cohort based on a hash of the remote IP address and current time, such that an IP address changes its cohort roughly every hour.\n"
"It declares no `@Priority`."
msgstr "有一个默认分类器，它根据远程 IP 地址的哈希值和当前时间来分配用户群组，使得一个 IP 地址大约每小时更换一次用户群组。该分类器未声明 `@Priority` 。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It is possible to define custom implementations of the `RequestClassifier` interface.\n"
"The implementations must be CDI beans, otherwise they are ignored.\n"
"The CDI rules of typesafe resolution must be followed.\n"
"That is, if multiple implementations exist with a different `@Priority` value and some of them are ``@Alternative``s, only the alternatives with the highest priority value are retained.\n"
"If no implementation is an alternative, all implementations are retained and are sorted in descending `@Priority` order (highest priority value comes first)."
msgstr "可以定义 `RequestClassifier` 接口的自定义实现。这些实现必须是 CDI Bean，否则将被忽略。必须遵循 CDI 类型安全解析规则。也就是说，如果存在多个具有不同 `@Priority` 值的实现，且其中部分是 `@Alternatives` ，则仅保留优先级最高的替代方案。 如果没有实现是替代项，则保留所有实现，并按 `@Priority` 值从高到低排序（优先级最高的值排在最前）。"

#. type: Title =
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Limitations"
msgstr "限制"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The load shedding extension currently only applies to HTTP requests, and is heavily skewed towards request/response network interactions.\n"
"This means that gRPC, WebSocket and other kinds of streaming over HTTP are not supported.\n"
"Other \"entrypoints\" to Quarkus applications, such as messaging, are not supported either."
msgstr "目前，负载分流功能的扩展仅适用于 HTTP 请求，且主要侧重于请求/响应类型的网络交互。这意味着 gRPC、WebSocket 以及其他基于 HTTP 的流式传输方式均不被支持。Quarkus 应用程序的其他“入口点”（例如消息传递）也不被支持。"

#. type: Plain text
#. mt: deepl
#: _versions/3.33/guides/load-shedding-reference.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Further, the load shedding implementation is currently rather basic and not heavily tested in production.\n"
"Improvements may be necessary."
msgstr "此外，目前限电功能的实现还比较基础，且在生产环境中尚未经过充分测试。可能需要进行改进。"

